                    </div>
                    <div class="collapsible-body">
                        <span>We ask every church to commit at least one Sunday a year to advocating to see that every child has a family as part of their weekly services. There are lots of ways to make this fit in an annual church calendar, but we know without meaningful intentionality by local church leadership the body of Christ will not be mobilized. We know that if every church makes this commitment, we can solve this crisis together in every community. 111Project would be honored to support and partner with you with resources, videos, training, and action plans to help you mobilize your congregation in a deeper and more impactful way. 111Project believes this ministry is less about solving the child welfare crisis and more about helping the local church make disciples that follow Jesus. Romans 10:14-15</span>
                    </div>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <div class="collapsible-header">
                        <i class="material-icons">keyboard_arrow_down</i>
                        <h5>Pledge for the Purpose</h4>
                    </div>
                    <div class="collapsible-body">
                        <span>Would you join us in this purpose? To mobilize the local church to see that every child has a family. We believe that some of the biggest displays of the gospel at work is the local church uniting and solving what seems to be unsolvable. We know this work will be difficult, it will be messy, and it can’t be done alone by any one congregation in any community. It will take leadership from a core group of community orientated congregations. We believe these efforts will lead to the sanctification and unity of the body of Christ in a pure undefiled way that only comes when we work together to serve vulnerable children and families as we would if we were serving Jesus. Matthew 25:35-36. 
                            
                        Simply if 1000 of our 6200 churches committed to recruit and support 1 family every year for this purpose of foster care in Oklahoma we see a shortage of families in Oklahoma resolved. If these same 1000 churches helped support and connect to 1 family every month through our CarePortal platform we see a community engaged to see children and families who are involved in child welfare supported. This is the heartbeat of 111Project. 1 Church 1 Family 1 Purpose.</span>
